@lap v0.3
# Machine-readable API spec. Each @endpoint block is one API call.
@api MongoDB Atlas Administration API
@base https://cloud.mongodb.com
@version 2.0
@auth Bearer digest | OAuth2
@common_fields {envelope: bool=False # Flag that indicates whether Application wraps the response in an `envelope` JSON object. Some API clients cannot access the HTTP response headers or status code. To remediate this, set envelope=true in the query. Endpoints that return a list of results use the results object as an envelope. Application adds the status parameter to the response body.}
@endpoints 504
@hint download_for_search
@toc api(504)

